    Date: Mon, 9 Nov 87 17:49:35 PST
    From: nowicki@Sun.COM (Bill Nowicki)

    Here are my two cents:

    WILDCARDS

       There are really at least four kinds of wildcards:

There are others, if you let data be stored in objects instead of having
RRs attached to names.

But this begs a larger question: What are wildcards in the current
domain system for?  From what I can tell, the only thing they are used
for is for storing default MX records.  (I agree there may be other
possible uses, but this is the only one anybody seems to use.)  My
counter to that is: Let's figure out how mail /should/ work and then
design something to meet those goals.  What we seem to be doing is
trying to shoehorn something the domain system to enable a currently
rigid mail path determination.

